          h2.headline-2 Compliant and HITRUST certified Kubernetes in 10 minutes
          p.lead Datica automatically configures your underlying infrastructure, installs and configures a highly available Kubernetes cluster, and connects that cluster to Datica’s Cloud Compliance Management System — all in 10 minutes.
      .row.align-center.small-up-1.medium-up-2.large-up-4.group
        .column
          img src="https://images.ctfassets.net/189dvqdsjh46/yc639CSDwka8aAs4Uo0kW/cb3458e6089ae9bd7312389acc374f9b/setup-1.png?w=450" alt="Setup"
          p First we collect information about your cloud provider, required infrastructure to run your deployments, and how redundant you want the master cluster to be (HA by default).
        .column
          img src="https://images.ctfassets.net/189dvqdsjh46/4jQ7VNUSIMUIS2aIKQWEOO/bb83fc6ec264ddd12f3b29410fe784c0/setup-2.png?w=450" alt="Installation"
          p With the required information, Datica installs a new Kubernetes cluster into your account (or into Datica’s account, your choice).
        .column
          img src="https://images.ctfassets.net/189dvqdsjh46/3MKy2SJ2dWUQIWy8yKEK4C/85c4531dfb35b5a9a6c008939ede8f74/setup-3.png?w=450" alt="Verification"
          p Once the cluster is installed, and all system-level configurations are set, the Platform will begin continuously pulling the cluster’s running state and compare that to the required compliance state.
        .column
          img src="https://images.ctfassets.net/189dvqdsjh46/4GOXaSvKfu6SeaMmmw2k6i/241b016e86591f5b871a192c4583b48e/setup-4.png?w=450" alt="Done!"
